The EU and Russia have concluded a bilateral Wood Agreement in the context of Russia's WTO Accession. This Agreement lays down the basic provisions for EU imports of spruce and pine from Russia under tariff-rate quotas (TRQs) which provide for reduced export duties within the quotas. Imports under the TRQs have started in late 2012, but many issues still remain, namely a discriminatory list of exporters allowed to export under the TRQs, problems of tariff classification, wood sorting requirements as well as administrative issues. The quotas are severely underused (at a level of only 10-15%)
